						<summary>

						<p>On a stone near the temple of Rāmaliṅgēśvara on the outskirts of the village.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II (?), A.D. 1385.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1306, <hi rend="italic">Raktākshi, Māgha,</hi> śu. 5, Monday, corresponding to 1385 A.D., January 16.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of a well for providing water for the sacred bath of the god and the attendant deities by the palanquin-bearer <hi rend="italic">(besta)</hi> Nāgana-bōya, son of Yelle-bōya.</p>						

						</summary>
